data.title: Service does not match the food
data.text:
It's really too bad the food was very good and the restaurant offers a very nice ambiance. The service was horrendous from the moment we walked in the servers acted as if we were inconveniencing them.
 It took 10 minutes to be noticed for a drink order when we initially sat down, an additional 15 to have our orders taken, 4 requests to have jalapeños brought to the table, and 30 minutes after completing our meal to receive the check. No one checked on us during our meal or asked if we wanted more beverages.
This is really to bad that the service overshadowed everything else.

data.title: A slice of Mexico in downtown Santa Barbara
data.text: Great food, very nice service and a unique atmosphere is the offering in this place. The restaurant is located in a courtyard which creates a feeling of sitting in a Mexican village, especially after dark. The food is great and portions quite large and the guacamole was prepared by the table - very nice.

data.title: Price Performer
data.text: Our meal was simple and delicious.  We ordered table side guacamole and the seafood enchiladas.  The service was very good and we enjoyed the outdoor patio setting.  Would definitely go back.

data.title: Unfortunate
data.text:
This restaurant used to be my wife's favorite places to eat. We took the kids this weekend. My wife was embarrassed and apologetic about how poor our service and food was. 
Our server would pull a disappearing act on us. When we needed more water, napkins, chips, the bill, anything - she was no where to be found. The restaurant is not that big, not a lot of places to hide. Another server had to give us our bill and cash us out. 
The food was below average. For the prices they charge, I expect more than average.
It was a shame. They used to be much better than this.

data.title: Best Brunch
data.text: Outstanding quality food and very good service. We found the place by chance and will return for sure.  The variety and quality of the food is top notch. My wife and I had their brunch at around 11am on Sunday morning. They have everything from omelets, to fresh veggies, pork, chicken sausage, eggs Benedict, all the very best Mexican food on the planet. Great for families or just two!

data.title: excellent food
data.text:
we loved the location in an arcade and the atmosphere was relaxed. we had a super meal and the service was quick and friendly.
what a great find - the restaurant had character and a feeling of space! a lovely light and airy place to eat and the glass roof meant that you felt like outside dining!
I can definitely recommend this restaurant and if you like Mexican food the quality is so good!

data.title: Margarita Mondays !!!
data.text: Go on Monday night, for cheap margaritas and great Mexican comfort food.  Good prices, VERY friendly servers, and a quiet, delightful courtyard.  In the middle of everything, but off the beaten path.

data.title: Delicious
data.text: Lovely meal after a long drive. Great service, lovely venue, delicious margaritas and delicious fajitas! Definitely recommended!

data.title: Superb food in a beautiful atmosphere
data.text: We were glad that we found this place, hidden in an arcade, as we had here the best meal over our seven-day stay in Santa Barbara.  The patio is everything that you can imagine and then some, with a large magnolia tree on one side and a fountain trickling in the middle.  The high ceiling and beautiful balcony create a picture-perfect sight.  Best of all is the food and the value.  I ordered two appetizers for my meal (each would have been sufficient for me as a main course) and they were both beautifully cooked of the finest ingredients.  My husband had the chicken fajitas which he thought was the best meal he had had in Santa Barbara.  I can't recommend this place too highly.  Go!  By the way - while we were there for dinner there was a bridal party at a large table arrangement seating about 40 - all Spanish speaking, and a party of 12 ladies of a certain age - all English-speaking.  Each group was obviously enjoying themselves immensely.  And - don't forget to order the margarita special, a true delight.

data.title: Best Taco Tuesday!
data.text: $8.95 for all you can eat Taco bar. Great prices and great tacos. One of the best Mexican food places in town and extremely underrated.

data.title: Ole!
data.text: Such a pretty restaurant and you cannot beat the Taco Tuesday offerings.  I love the location in the Presidio Neighborhood and the service is friendly.  The food is fresh and a genuine value as well.

data.title: May be best Mexican food in SB
data.text: What's not to like?Huge,open space(roof opens-weather permitting).Guacamole fixed table-side with fresh chips continually prepared within sight.Dinner fresh ingredients and very tasty.The bar's special margarita is a must as well.

data.title: Great atmosphere for Large and Small Parties, Alike
data.text: After visiting El Paseo, I can recommend this restaurant for large parties and small parties, alike. The menu was very diverse and everything was delicious. We especially enjoyed the courtyard atmosphere and friendly staff. I called for a reservation and left a message. My call was promptly returned and our reservation accommodated. Our server, Denise F., provided table side guacamole and was helpful with menu choices. There was a very large party (family reunion) dining there at the same time, yet our server was still very attentive and available. We will be back!

data.title: So authentic!!
data.text: El Paseo is a wonderful restaurant. The food was delicious and very authentic. Not your main stream Americanized Mexican food. The bar area is also huge and the margaritas very strong :). We were there for a business event and had the entire restaurant rented out but the service was still excellent. I would love to go back and dine on a regular night. I heard from many people in the area that Taco Tuesday is wonderful too!!

data.title: Fabulous brunch buffet
data.text: The food is amazing - homemade tortillas, enchiladas, tamales, chimichangas - but the margaritas are even better!  Everything was delicious - we will be back.

data.title: Horrible service
data.text:
Took 28 people here for dinner for a special event. Had a RSVP here for months as we wanted to make sure we had a place to have dinner. 
This was quite honestly the worst service I have ever had at a restaursnt.  I spoke with the very nice manager twice but she couldn't help. They were so short staffed that out group had 1 server and she brought 2 plates out of the kitchen at a time. She had no help at all, we had food and drinks on our bill that we didn't order and/or never received.  The manager told me that she was powerless and the owners do the scheduling. Well, the owners or schedulers are responsible for this honest review.  I would NOT ever take a group of more than 2 to this restaurant again if I ever go back.  The food was good, the drinks were good but it took forever to get out order taken and to receive anything. Our server had several other tables including ours.  Do yourself a favor, keep looking, there are many awesome restaurants in Santa Barbara....don't go here!

data.title: Feeding the masses
data.text: If you have a gang of kids go for Taco Tuesday.  It's fun and lively.  Also, if you have a gang of kids, you'll need a margarita.  Delish.

data.title: Best Mexican food in SB!
data.text: This restaurant is tucked away in the El Paseo shopping area, a historic building where they have celebrated Fiesta for 90 years.  The drinks are always good, the fajitas are excellent, and the tortillas are home-made.  The manager always makes you feel like family.  Open air in good weather (almost always) and they close the roof in rainy weather.  Get the fresh guacamole prepared at your table.

data.title: Wonderful experience @ El Paseo
data.text: Had the most enjoyable meal at this restaurant.  The Atmosphere is excellent and the food is even better and it felt like we in Old Mexico.  Open air seating and great service was fun and relaxing.

data.title: taco buffet not ok
data.text: Me and a group of friends decided to go to El Paseo for Taco Tuesday which I did not know it was a buffet. The place was full & the drinks were very good. I went to the buffet & to my surprise there were no sneeze guards in any part of the buffet. The food was in Chafing Dishes but the covers were open as many people go through the line, the condiments had no covers at all. I use to work in a restaurant & on buffets we always had sneeze guards, it was a policy for us. I only had the buffet & did not have any other item for the menu. To make a long story short, the Taco buffet food was not tasty & I did not have a good night. Maybe it was the fact that the price for the buffet was only $7.00, I would rather pay more & have better food & covers on all food.
